BIO
3x Grammy award-winning superstar, Lizzo has become a household name with over 5 billion global streams and a platinum selling debut album to date. With the help of anthemic smash hits like the 7x Platinum ‚ÄúTruth Hurts,‚Äù the 3x Platinum ‚ÄúGood As Hell,‚Äù and the 2x Platinum ‚ÄúJuice,‚Äù Lizzo released her Nice Life Recording Company/Atlantic Records debut album CUZ I LOVE YOU on April 19th 2019, debuting at #6 on the Billboard Top 200 Albums chart and spending 24 consecutive weeks in the chart‚Äôs Top 10. ‚ÄúTruth Hurts‚Äù became the longest running #1 by a solo female rap artist in history after spending seven weeks atop the charts. Since the release of the meteoric CUZ I LOVE YOU, Lizzo has been named both Time Magazine and Entertainment Weekly‚Äôs 2019 Entertainer of the Year as well as gracing the covers of Rolling Stone, Billboard‚Äôs GRAMMY Preview Issue, British Vogue, Elle‚Äôs Women In Music Issue, and many others.  Additionally, Lizzo kicked off 2020 with a showstopping opening performance at the 62nd Annual GRAMMY awards and took home three big wins, in addition to being the most-nominated artist of the year. 2020 has also seen her win the awards for Best Female R&B/Pop Artist at the 2020 B.E.T Awards and both ‚ÄúEntertainer of the Year‚Äù and ‚ÄúOutstanding Video‚Äù at the 2020 NAACP Awards. Her list of high profile TV performances also include the 2019 American Music Awards, VMAs, B.E.T Awards and Saturday Night Live, in addition to in depth profiles on CBS This Morning‚Äôs GRAMMY primetime special and CBS Sunday Morning. Now, Lizzo returns with her first new single in two years- the highly-anticipated ‚ÄúRumors" featuring Cardi B.

description:
"Ich habe die Angst, meinen Mann oder meinen Sohn nicht mehr zu erkennen." ‚Äì Yvonne, 42, hat Alzheimer. Als Yvonne immer h√§ufiger ihr Handy verlegt und Passw√∂rter vergisst, ist die Familie nicht allzu beunruhigt. Doch bei der Arbeit f√§llt noch mehr auf, dass Yvonne nicht mehr so leistungsf√§hig ist wie fr√ºher. Ihre Arbeitskolleg:innen wenden sich besorgt an ihren Mann: Yvonne sei zunehmend verwirrt, man m√ºsse etwas unternehmen. Die Untersuchung in der Uniklinik Frankfurt ergibt schlie√ülich die unfassbare Diagnose: Alzheimer im Fr√ºhstadium - mit gerade mal 42 Jahren.

Alzheimer trifft nicht nur alte Menschen. Bei etwa jedem 100. Fall tritt die Krankheit schon sehr fr√ºh auf ‚Äì manche bekommen sie schon mit Ende 30. Anders als beim "normalen" Alzheimer ist meist ein Gendefekt Ursache des fr√ºhen Ausbruchs. Der geistige Verfall l√§uft dann ab wie im Zeitraffer. Marc und vor allem sein Vater m√ºssen zusehen, wie Yvonne immer kranker wird. Marc muss nicht nur damit fertig werden, dass seine Mutter immer vergesslicher wird. Aufgrund eines Gen-Tests bei seiner Mutter steht fest, dass auch er das fatale Alzheimer-Gen vererbt bekommen haben k√∂nnte - mit einer Wahrscheinlichkeit von 50 Prozent.

channelTitle: In The Fast Lane With Jamie
channelDescription: Have you ever felt like it's just too late to make a change in your life? Well, I'm 40 years old and I've already accomplished 1 dream of mine, to own a successful auto repair shop built from honest values and high quality work. I'm still the owner of Elite Motor Works and now I'm on a mission to prove it's not too late to chase your dreams. To make a change, you need to shift gears, change lanes and take action. That's where the channel name comes from, you have to be in the fast lane to move past the average daily driver. I've always loved photography and making videos from a very young age. I also love educating and entertaining others. So I've set my new life goal to make videos that will entertain and educate you in everything automotive. Please join me in this journey and lets show people its still possible to be successful to start something new, even at 40.
